title: Australia Battles Severe Floods as Girl Is Seriously Injured by Lightning Strike
description: Severe storms and flash flooding are pounding Queensland, Australia, in the wake of Tropical Cyclone Jasper.

title: North Korea Fires Ballistic Missile Into the Sea as South Korea, U.S. Step Up Deterrence Plans
description: North Korea fired a ballistic missile into the sea, South Korea said, amid steps by U.S. and Seoul to step up nuclear deterrence plans against North Korean threats.

title: The Attacks From Yemen’s Houthi Rebels in the Red Sea Are Having a Significant Global Impact
description: Yemen's Houthi Rebels have escalated their attacks since the Israel-Hamas war, vowing to attack all ships stopping at Israeli ports.

title: European Ministers Call For a ‘Sustainable Ceasefire’ in Gaza. Here’s What That Means
description: U.K. and Germany's foreign ministers said they support a “sustainable ceasefire” in the Israel-Hamas war.

title: The Quest for Racial Equality Has Always Been Different for Rural Americans
description: Even as the civil rights revolution brought significant gains to Black residents of cities, the story was very different in rural places.

title: Over 60 People Have Drowned After Migrant Vessel Capsizes Off Libya, U.N. Says
description: A boat carrying dozens of migrants trying to reach Europe capsized off the coast of Libya, leaving more than 60 people dead, the U.N. said.
